<div type="translation" resp="part:emfr">
                
                
<p n="1">
                        Prosperity! Fortune!
                </p>
                
                
<p n="1-2">
                        Sixteen year of the victorious king Dantivarman.
                </p>
                
                
<p n="2-5">
                        I, Kuvāvaṉ Cāttaṉ, alias Viṭēlviṭuku Muttaraiyaṉ, having scooped the hill 
<supplied reason="subaudible">at</supplied> Tiruvāvattūr as a temple and having installed the lord 
<supplied reason="explanation">
<foreign>
<hi rend="grantha">bhaṭā</hi>rar</foreign>
<note>That is, Skt. 
<foreign>bhaṭṭa</foreign>.</note> </supplied>, this temple 
<gap reason="illegible" /> the members of the 
<foreign>nāṭu</foreign> assembly of the Eastern Ceṅkaḷināṭu 
<gap reason="illegible" /> that 
<gap reason="illegible" /> has done for/to the members of the 
<foreign>nāṭu</foreign> 
<gap reason="illegible" />
                </p>
       
         </div>

        
<div type="commentary">                
<p>Note on the identity of Kuvāvaṉ Cāttaṉ. See IP, fn1.</p>
                
<p>Note on Ceṅkaḻināṭu. See IP, fn2.</p>
